comments: Muscala (BOS) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Antetokounmpo's (MIL) layup attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) brings his off-arm toward Muscala (BOS) and marginal contact occurs during the layup attempt.
Antetokounmpo's (MIL) shot attempt does not touch the basket and he is the first player to touch the ball. A traveling violation is correctly called.
Ingles (MIL) moves alongside White's (BOS) path and absorbs the marginal body contact during the driving shot attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) goes to, not through, White's (BOS) space and marginal contact occurs as Antetokounmpo releases away on the post spin move.
White (BOS) initiates contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Allen (MIL) legally contests Hauser's (BOS) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
White (BOS) and Holiday (MIL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs before Holiday cleanly taps the ball back to his teammates.
Muscala (BOS) retracts his arm from Antetokounmpo's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

White (BOS) dives to the floor to recover the loose ball and calls timeout prior to Holiday (MIL) making contact with the ball on his tie up attempt. White does not re-establish a new pivot foot or travel when regaining possession.
Williams (BOS) commits a take foul on Holiday (MIL).
White (BOS) takes longer than 5 seconds to release his inbounds pass.
Middleton (MIL) legally contests Hauser's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Muscala (BOS) and Middleton (MIL) briefly come together and marginal contact occurs as Middleton spins away during the inbound.
Muscala (BOS) adjusts to Middleton's (MIL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Muscala (BOS) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Hauser (BOS) is moving alongside Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Hauser (BOS) initiates contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm, which affects his post-shot attempt.
Allen (MIL) makes clean contact with the ball as he attempts to steal the ball from Hauser (BOS).
Holiday (MIL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from White (BOS) prior to any incidental follow-through contact occurring.
After the steal, Brogdon (BOS) brushes Holiday's (MIL) arm and marginal contact occurs as he begins to move in transition.
White (BOS) contests Holiday's (MIL) dunk attempt and any contact during the play at the basket is marginal.
Williams (BOS) establishes himself in Holiday's (MIL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Connaughton (MIL) and Muscala (BOS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Connaughton (MIL) legally contests Muscala's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any foot to foot contact after the release is deemed incidental as Muscala slightly extends his leg forward.
Muscala's (BOS) shot attempt goes directly out of bounds and possession is correctly awarded to the Bucks.

Brogdon (BOS) extends his forearm and initiates contact with Allen's (MIL) body, which affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt. A shooting foul is correctly assessed as the illegal contact occurs after Allen's gather on his drive that originates outside of and ends inside the LDB.
Allen (MIL) initiates contact with Hauser (BOS), which affects his FOM as the screen is set.
Connaughton (MIL) and Muscala (BOS) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Carter (MIL) initiates contact with Brogdon's (BOS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Connaughton (MIL) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Williams's (BOS) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Muscala (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Antetokounmpo (MIL) at the end of the drive.
Muscala (BOS) brings his hands toward Allen (MIL) and marginal contact occurs as Muscala releases away to roll.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes clean hand on ball contact and dislodges it away from Williams (BOS) prior to any incidental follow-through contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) engages with White (BOS) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Antetokounmpo releases away to retrieve the inbounds pass.
After communicating with the replay center, it is determined that the foul by White (BOS) meets the criteria for a clear path foul.
